Police in Migori County have arrested a man said to have hacked his disabled son to death on Tuesday evening.  The suspect is said to have attacked the 10-year-old with a machete. The boy died on the spot.  Angry residents attacked the suspect and wanted to lynch him before the police rescued him.  The man has been locked up at Kehancha Police Station as detectives launched investigations into the incident. Help us serve you better by completing our quick survey. County police commander Mark Wanjala said they were yet to establish the motive of the attack.  Police officer kills colleague in Laikipia  Suspect in the murder of four in Kitengela to detained for 10 days, court says  Prime suspect behind murder of four men in Kitengela arrested  IPOA, DPP crack whip on suspects of Kianjokoma brothers’ death  “We have launched investigations into the incident,” he said.   Wafugaji kuku Migori kunufaika iwapo pendekezo la kujengwa kwa kiwanda cha kuku litatekelezwa  Murder Mystery: FBI joins investigations into the disappearance & murder of Bashir Mohammed  Police detain a couple and their son for allegedly beating their 15-year-old daughter to death By James Omoro | 1 day ago By Sammy Omingo | 1 day ago By Harold Odhiambo | 4 days ago By Kevine Omollo  | 5 days ago